name: Cover Buzz 7"
description:
If you ever wanted a sign of how co-operative and creative UK independent labels and bands can be, then ‘Cover Buzz’ must surely be a rather decent example.

Whilst all four bands usually turn in damn fine tirades of HM2blastcore (Let It Die), Turmoil-meets-Torche (Pariso), Envy meets Fucked Up (MINE) and ‘Hopesfall play stadium crust’ (Svalbard) this release signifies something very different indeed.

Made to look and feel like an old jazz record for no apparent reason other than it looks fucking awesome - this is a cover versions 7 inch that celebrates punk, hardcore and powerviolence, perhaps even highlighting some classic and modern bands that fans of these bands might not have been previously aware of.

Limited to a one-time pressing of 250 copies on jukebox vinyl, this release acts as a great assertion of the strength and diversity displayed between friends in bands and record labels. No bullshit, just lots of fun and even more great music.

Tracks: 
Let It Die - War In The Head (7 Seconds) 
Pariso - Straight Hypocrisy Images (Witch Cult / Weekend Nachos) 
Svalbard - This Is The End (Victims) 
MINE - Everybody Hates Me (Tear It Up)

Full stream - http://dogknightsproductions.bandcamp.com/album/dk046-pariso-svalbard-mine-let-it-die-cover-buzz-7-ep

name: Vinyl Mega Bundle - 3 for £20
Consanguinity - New Album - Vinyl
description:
Returning a little over a year after their debut album ‘Nothing Beyond Everything After’, Pariso have somehow warped the space-time continuum and produced ‘Consanguinity’ - a record that shows an evolution far greater than (approximately) 365 days should allow.

Loosely based on the theme of family and relations, ‘Consanguinity’ displays highs of atmosphere, melody and thought amidst Pariso's trademark ferocity and aggression. Produced by Lewis Johns at The Ranch and rife with the flair of new-ish guitarist Alex Heffernan, this album should leave no doubts in the mind of any discerning, forward-thinking heavy music fan.

Consanguinity is available now on 12" vinyl (with an exclusive vinyl-only bonus track) and as a free download. No pre-order, no build up, no hype.

name: Nothing Beyond Everything After - Vinyl Album
description:
Pariso deliver their definitive manifesto to date, Nothing Beyond Everything After. Having forged an infamous history of split 5"s, credit card shaped CDs and floppy discs, Pariso have now delivered a 12 song, 30 minute record that truly delivers upon the bursts of promise their past has always threatened.

'Nothing Beyond Everything After' is a focussed blast that shows nods to everyone from Slayer to Mastodon to power-violence, black metal and much more - all the while sticking to the framework of fast, concise, ultra-heavy dissonant hardcore. Recorded by Jamie Frye and mastered by Lewis Johns, this is an album designed to be played on vinyl and engaged with accordingly.

As much care has gone into the packaging as with all other aspects of this record, which is housed in extra heavy casebound sleeves with matte finish, printed inners and is available on two incredible colour variations.

Pre-orders includes a free download of The Huntsman with the full digital album being sent out a week before the release date.

Pressing Info

250 / Sky Blue with Purple Haze 
100 / Limited Edition 'Stella' Vinyl

Tracklist

05. Native Wolves 
06. Leeches 
07. The Huntsman 
08. Lonely Battle 
09. Nothing Beyond Everything After 
10. Unmitigated Sky 
11. Omerta 
12. Officeress

name: 2009-2011 Discography
description:
Everything we have ever recorded, up until the 'Nothing Beyond Everything After' album.

This includes the untitled 'square' 7", the 'I'd Rather Die Than Go To Heaven' floppy disc, the split 5" with Kerouac, the 'Sooner Insignificant Better' 7", the split tape with We'll Die Smiling and the split 7" with Manuscripts as well as covers by Three Trapped Tigers, Obituary, Hatebreed, Crystal Castles and Eyehategod. 24 tracks in total.

Thanks to the guys at Animal Defence Records (www.facebook.com/AnimalDefenceRecords) this discography has finally seen a physical release on white and white/purple marble effect vinyl LP. 

Includes download code

name: Black Milk 2012 - Vinyl Postcard
description:
*TEMPORARILY OUT OF STOCK - GETTING MORE STOCK IN SOON!*

Black Milk is a track that originally appeared on our debut Split 7" with Manuscripts; now re-recorded during the album sessions for Nothing Beyond Everything After.

This is only available as a postcard flexi disc vinyl. Which is exactly what it sounds like - it's is a postcard, it's also a record. Not only that but it comes with a download that includes two brand new tracks, recorded in August 2012, "Mother's Talons" and "Cold Venom". For £2. Ridiculous.
